Cybercrime was the thing that surprised me the most because most cybercrimes do not demand complex technical knowledge, it takes advantage of human's carelessness. Attackers are tricking user to disclose private information such as passwords, account numbers by either fishing email or fakeUPIlink. Moreover, I am very shocked that most student/young generation are becoming victim of this cybercrime, it seems that this will be a serious problem.

Due to this task, the thing I will do from now on is always check carefully before clicking on a link or replying to a message/email/application. I will always check for emails, website, transaction link, etc. Whether it is original or not before sending my personal detail or paying to it. This is a small but helpful change and could be reduced number of victim significantly.
